The paper proposes a method for multimodal data fusion using tensor factorization and neural networks. This work involves machine learning and data analysis, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a method for regularizing neural networks to avoid overfitting. The second likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper applies the proposed method to sentiment analysis and emotion recognition tasks. The third likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper involves processing visual and textual data. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper proposes a method for improving the performance of neural networks. The fifth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), as the paper involves processing multiple modalities of data.
